item.title: Help With Changing Something In A Client
item.dc:creator: @xx_qwertyuiop_xx xx qwertyuiop xx
item.description:
@xx_qwertyuiop_xx wrote:

Chaosscape:

i think that might be the problem but when i click complie it says system can not find specifed path am i missing something for it

You need to set your path to the bin folder of your version of JDK.

@echo off
"C:\program files\java\jdk1.6.0.##\bin\javac.exe" *.java
pause

That’s what your compiler should look like. Change the #s to the version you have.
You can find out what version of JDK you have by going to your java folder in program files and looking at the numbers in the folder name.
If you don’t have a folder named JDK, google it and download it from sun’s website.
